The problem involves finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_7\) is the seventh order statistic in a sample of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). This means \(P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7\), and since the distribution is continuous, \(P(X < 27.3) = 0.7\).

The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to at least seven of the eight observations being less than 27.3. Let \(K\) be the number of observations less than 27.3. Then \(K\) follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\). Thus, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(K \geq 7) = P(K = 7) + P(K = 8)\).

Calculate each probability:
- \(P(K = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3\)
- \(P(K = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = (0.7)^8\)

Compute the powers:
- \((0.7)^7 = 0.0823543\)
- \((0.7)^8 = 0.05764801\)

Then:
- \(P(K = 7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032\)
- \(P(K = 8) = 0.05764801\)

Sum the probabilities:
- \(P(K \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833\)

