- Total patients: 100 (for percentage calculation).
- High blood pressure: 16%.
- Low blood pressure: 19%.
- Normal blood pressure: 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.
- Irregular heartbeat: 17%.
- Of those with irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure: 35% of 17% = 0.35 × 17 = 5.95% (irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure).
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have irregular heartbeat: 11% of 65% = 0.11 × 65 = 7.15% (irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure).

The total percentage with irregular heartbeat is the sum of those with irregular heartbeat and high, normal, or low blood pressure:
- Irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure: 5.95%.
