Solution: The first urn contains 8 red and 7 blue balls, for a total of 15 balls. The second urn contains \( r \) red balls and 9 blue balls, for a total of \( r + 9 \) balls.

The probability of drawing two balls of the same color is the sum of the probabilities of both being red or both being blue.

