Solution: The dissociation energy \(D_e\) is calculated from the given \(D_0 = 2.4287 \, \text{eV}\), \(\nu_e / c = 1405.65 \, \text{cm}^{-1}\) (which is \(\omega_e\)), and \(\nu_e x_e / c = 23.20 \, \text{cm}^{-1}\) (which is \(\omega_e x_e\)).

The zero-point energy \(G(0)\) for the anharmonic oscillator is given by:
\[
G(0) = \frac{1}{2} \omega_e - \frac{1}{4} \omega_e x_e
\]
Substituting the values:
\[
G(0) = \frac{1}{2} \times 1405.65 - \frac{1}{4} \times 23.20 = 702.825 - 5.80 = 697.025 \, \text{cm}^{-1}
\]

Convert \(G(0)\) from \(\text{cm}^{-1}\) to eV using the conversion factor \(1 \, \text{cm}^{-1} = 1.23984 \times 10^{-4} \, \text{eV}\):
\[
